    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1917-09-05T09:29:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1917-09-05T09:29:00-05:00" n="144"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d144">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 861.51/202</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Russia</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_FDR1"
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Francis</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram—Extract]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Petrograd</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-09-05T18:00:00+03:31">
                            <hi rend="italic">September 5, 1917, 6 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received September 8, 7.30 a.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1706. … Internal situation again threatening. Extreme socialists more aggressive
                    demanding removal of generals, claiming threatened counter [-revolution?]
                    justifies same. Had interview with <persName corresp="#p_KAF1"
                        >Kerensky</persName> yesterday, endeavored to impress upon him necessity for
                    restoring discipline; to-day he promulgates proclamation appealing for support
                    of officers which first word utterances by him in that line.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_FDR1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Francis</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
